div.p:
As to the Second Obſervation, That plenty of Money and Riches is the genuine Effect and Product of Trade; 
                  Object. 2
               The Value of Credit. this we readily grant: But by the Gentlemans Favour, Credit is the Cauſa ſine qua non; No Nation was ever known to grow rich by Trade, where the Current or Intercourſe by Credit is ſtopt; and that Credit, which is the Primum Movens, or chief Engine of Trade, can ruine it, I confeſs to me is a Paradox. But the Gentleman ſaith further, That theſe Tallyes are Copper, and of a fictitious Value, to be decreed only from a new Statute. I am afraid the Legiſlators of Scotland have diſobliged this Gentleman: I thought only an Act of Parliament had been all that a reaſonable Man can deſire, in order to confirm his Title; and for my part, I ſhall never ſeek after a better Title to any Eſtate I have, if I have only an Act of Parliament to confirm the ſame to me and mine.
